-- Deutsche Bank hires Credit Suisse banker for India investment banking role-sources   
-- By Sumeet Chatterjee
-- Thu Apr 10, 2014 11:16PM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, April 11 (Reuters) - Deutsche Bank AG <DBKGn.DE> has hired senior Credit Suisse Group AG <CSGN.VX> investment banker, Rahul Chawla, to head its structured finance business in India, two sources with direct knowledge of the development said.

Mumbai-based Chawla, who as the head of Credit Suisse' global market solutions group in India was in charge of equity and debt capital market transactions and structured finance deals, had joined the Swiss bank in 2007 from Deutsche Bank.